text.tspan: This measure tell us how many years of education a child of school entrance age can expect to receive if the current
age-specific enrolment rates persist throughout the child’s years of schooling.
The width of each bar corresponds to the number of children that are 7 years old.
Children that are 7 years old (close to school-entrance-age in most countries)
Source: UNDP, HDR (2018), United Nations – Population Division (2019 Revision)
